body:
I can reproduce with the default parser. Marking as accepted.

I think one option would just be to parenthesize the alternate during autofix (unless already parenthesized). It would be ideal to only do so with yield and other keywords, but we do have `no-extra-parens` for handling extra parentheses that aren't needed.
I would love to help work on a fix. If I could get some mentorship, I would love to take a try at a fix. Would that be possible?

Hi @biw, I would be happy to help you out. If you have any questions as to go, you may leave comments here and a team member will help; additionally, you are welcome to visit the ESLint team chat on Gitter (https://gitter.im/eslint/eslint) or chat with me directly on that platform.

Welcome aboard and good luck as you get started!

EDIT: Also, here's a link to our [Pull Request guidelines](https://eslint.org/docs/developer-guide/contributing/pull-requests), in case you haven't seen those yet. Hope this helps!

issue.title: Fix: add parens for yield statement (fixes #10432)
